docs.lead_paragraph: Some one hundred members of the Austrian and Hungarian colonies of this city gave a dinner last night at the Hotel Astor to Rear Admiral Hermann Pleskott, commanding the two Austro-Hungarian warships that came in from the Jamestown Exposition last Sunday, and his staff.

headline.main: COUNTRYMEN FEAST ADMIRAL PLESKOTT; Austro-Hungarian Commander and His Staff Entertained at the Astor. NOVEL TABLE DECORATIONS Austro-Hungarian Shield Done In Ice with Electric Lights Frozen In It -- Visitors Warmly Cheered.

docs.abstract: 100 members of Austro-Hungarian community of NYC hon Rear Adm H Pleskott at dinner, Hotel Astor
